==Description==

On January 19, 2008 The Effortless Economy Institute was formed by Nathan Cravens with
the essay 'Toward an Effortless Economy'. It was
established to analyze trends in activities that produce within and outside traditional market models with a focus on methods practiced trending toward zero financial cost or with diminished effort. 



